BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 1: The Time Machine) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Twins Leo and Luna were exploring their grandpa's dusty attic one rainy afternoon.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Behind old boxes and cobwebs, they found something incredible - a strange machine!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (It had dials, buttons, and a screen that said 'DESTINATION: 230,000,000 YEARS AGO.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('It is a time machine!' Luna gasped. 'Should we try it?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Leo grinned. 'Absolutely! Let us visit the age of the dinosaurs!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (They climbed in, pressed the big green button, and WHOOOOSH - they were gone!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: HOW WE KNOW ABOUT DINOSAURS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Fossils are preserved remains or traces of ancient life \(bones, teeth, footprints\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Scientists called paleontologists dig up and study fossils to learn about the past.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Fossils form when an animal is buried quickly in sediment after death.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Over millions of years, minerals replace the bone, turning it to stone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (We can determine fossil ages using radioactive dating of the surrounding rock.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Dinosaurs lived during the Mesozoic Era: Triassic, Jurassic, and Cretaceous periods.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The word 'dinosaur' means 'terrible lizard' in Greek \(coined in 1842\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Over 1,000 different dinosaur species have been named so far!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* New dinosaur species are discovered about every 2 weeks somewhere in the world.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Make a fossil: press a shell or leaf into clay, remove it, fill the impression with plaster!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do we only find fossils of some animals and not all of them?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
