BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 147.6 720 Td (Chapter 3: Giants of the Jurassic) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The twins jumped forward in time to the Jurassic Period. The world had changed!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Suddenly, an ENORMOUS shadow fell over them. They looked up... and up... and UP!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (A Brachiosaurus towered above the trees - taller than a five-story building!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('It is as long as three school buses!' Leo whispered, amazed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The gentle giant munched on treetop leaves, unbothered by the tiny humans below.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (A herd of them moved slowly across the lush green landscape like living mountains.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: GIANT HERBIVORES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Sauropods were the largest land animals EVER - some over 100 feet long!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (They were herbivores \(plant-eaters\) with long necks to reach high treetops.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Brachiosaurus: 85 ft long, 40 ft tall, weighed 80 tons \(like 11 elephants!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Diplodocus: 90 ft long with a whip-like tail for defense against predators.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (They swallowed stones \(gastroliths\) to help grind food in their stomachs!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Their long necks let them eat from trees that other dinosaurs could not reach.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Sauropod footprints have been found that are over 5 feet across!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* The biggest sauropod \(Argentinosaurus\) may have weighed 100 tons!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Some sauropods may have lived 100+ years based on bone growth ring analysis.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Measure 85 feet outside \(about 28 big steps\). That is how long a Brachiosaurus was!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (How much food would a 100-foot-long animal need to eat every day?) Tj ET

endstream
