BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 181.2 720 Td (Chapter 5: Flying Reptiles) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Luna looked up and saw something incredible soaring through the Cretaceous sky.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (A Pteranodon glided overhead with wings wider than a small airplane!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Wait - are those flying dinosaurs?' Leo asked.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Actually no!' Luna corrected. 'Pterosaurs were flying reptiles, NOT dinosaurs!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('They lived alongside dinosaurs but belonged to a completely different group.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (The enormous creature swooped down toward the ocean, snatching fish from the waves.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: PTEROSAURS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Pterosaurs were flying reptiles that lived alongside dinosaurs - but were NOT dinosaurs!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Their wings were made of skin membrane stretched from an elongated finger to their body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Quetzalcoatlus had a 36-foot wingspan - as wide as a fighter jet!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Despite their size, many pterosaurs were surprisingly lightweight \(hollow bones\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Some pterosaurs were as small as sparrows; others were the largest flying animals ever.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (They went extinct along with the dinosaurs 66 million years ago.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Quetzalcoatlus stood as tall as a giraffe when on the ground!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Pterosaurs had excellent eyesight for hunting fish from high in the air.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* The first pterosaur fossil was discovered in 1784 in Germany.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Make a paper airplane. How is its 'wing' different from a bird's wing or a pterosaur's wing?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (What is the difference between pterosaurs, birds, and bats? They all fly differently!) Tj ET

endstream
