BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 195.60000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 6: Ocean Giants) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The time machine could also work underwater! The twins dove into the ancient sea.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Massive creatures swam through the dark water all around them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (A Mosasaurus glided past - 50 feet of powerful jaws and streamlined body!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('These are marine reptiles,' Luna explained. 'Also NOT technically dinosaurs.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Long-necked Plesiosaurs paddled gracefully with their four flippers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('The oceans were just as dangerous as the land!' Leo gulped.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: MARINE REPTILES) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Marine reptiles ruled the oceans while dinosaurs ruled the land.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Mosasaurus: 50 ft long, top predator of Cretaceous seas, ate sharks and fish.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Plesiosaur: long neck, four flippers, some were 40+ feet long.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Ichthyosaur: shaped like dolphins, could swim up to 22 mph, gave live birth!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (These ocean giants were air-breathing reptiles - they had to surface to breathe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (None of these marine reptiles were actually dinosaurs \(dinosaurs lived only on land\).) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Some Plesiosaurs had necks 23 feet long - half their total body length!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Loch Ness Monster legends may have been inspired by Plesiosaur fossils.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Mosasaurus is related to modern Komodo dragons and monitor lizards.) Tj ET
