BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 128.4 720 Td (Chapter 7: The Day Everything Changed) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The twins set the time machine to 66 million years ago - the day it all ended.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (A bright light streaked across the sky, growing larger and larger.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('The asteroid!' Luna whispered. 'It is about 7 miles wide, moving at 44,000 mph!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (They watched from the safety of the machine as it struck the Earth near Mexico.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The impact was unimaginable - 10 billion times more powerful than a nuclear bomb.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Dust filled the sky, blocking the Sun. Within months, most life on Earth would die.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: THE KT EXTINCTION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (66 million years ago, an asteroid about 7 miles wide hit what is now Mexico.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The impact created the Chicxulub crater - 110 miles wide and 12 miles deep!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Dust and debris blocked sunlight for months, causing a global 'winter.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Without sunlight, plants died. Without plants, herbivores starved. Then carnivores.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (About 75% of all species went extinct, including all non-bird dinosaurs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Evidence: a thin layer of rare element iridium found worldwide in 66-million-year-old rock.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The asteroid hit with the force of 10 billion Hiroshima bombs!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Tsunamis over 300 feet high swept across the globe after impact.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Small mammals survived by burrowing underground and eating insects/seeds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Drop a ball into a tray of flour/cocoa powder. See the 'crater' and 'debris' pattern it makes!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (If the asteroid had missed Earth, would dinosaurs still be alive today?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
